Israel Minister Says Wireless Fees May Drop 50%, Calcalist Says

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-02-23T06:35:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/israel-minister-says-wireless-fees-may-drop-50-calcalist-says.html
 Israeli mobile phone fees may drop
by 50 percent once newcomers enter the market, Israeli Minister
of Communications Moshe Kahlon said in an interview to the
financial daily Calcalist that was published today.    The two new wireless companies that  Israel  intends to
introduce to the local market will have to offer lower prices to
encourage Israelis to leave their current providers, he said.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gwen Ackerman at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net  